The paper deals with the problem of designing a forward link linear precoder for Massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The methodology proposed also involves the use of Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (OFDM) for frequency selective channels, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of Per-Group Processing (PGP) technique, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents simulation results, which is a topic related to computer science and networking (cs.COM).
